refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.description;
boolarray_walk_recursive arrayinput callbackfuncname mixeduserdata&null;
Applies the user-defined function funcname to each element of the input array. This function will recurse into deeper arrays.

  &reftitle.examples;



    array_walk_recursive example


<?php
$sweet = array('a' => 'apple', 'b' => 'banana');
$fruits = array('sweet' => $sweet, 'sour' => 'lemon');

function test_print($item, $key)
{
    echo "$key holds $item\n";
}

array_walk_recursive($fruits, 'test_print');
?>


    &example.outputs;


a holds apple
b holds banana
sour holds lemon




     You may notice that the key 'sweet' is never displayed. Any key that holds an
     array will not be passed to the function.
